CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 10, 1955, pg. 12 reads: "Receptions Climax Wests' 'Golden Year' - Highlights Of The Wests' Receptions - 'Tis seldom that a couple, married fifty years, celebrates the happy occasion with double receptions.  But that was the case when Mr. and Mrs. Thomas L. West Sr. observed their golden year with a home reception at 608 Duff Street on Monday, Sept. 5, and their sons, Thomas L. West Jr. and Raymond, feted them the following night at the north Side Elks.  Snapped during there social events were...Mrs. Rhoda Johnson kisses Mrs. Thomas L. West Sr.  at the reception given at the North Side Elks Tuesday night, while Mr. West and others' look on. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Rhoda Johnson, kissing Mrs. Thomas L. West Sr., standing next to Thomas L. West Sr. wearing dinner jacket, gathered with other men and women in North Side Elks for fiftieth wedding anniversary
